## Runtime (this setup) — MemPalace 3.1.0

The Cursor MCP server uses a **dedicated venv** (not Python 3.14):  
`%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\venvs\mempalace\Scripts\python.exe` — **Python 3.12** + **mempalace 3.1.0** (ChromaDB pinned by upstream to `>=0.5,<0.7`).

**Upgrade MemPalace in place:**

```powershell
& "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\venvs\mempalace\Scripts\python.exe" -m pip install --upgrade "mempalace==3.1.0"
```

Pin file for reference: `~/.cursor/requirements-mempalace-mcp.txt`.

**Why not Python 3.14 for MCP:** ChromaDB 0.6.x (required by mempalace 3.1.x) does not import cleanly on 3.14; the venv uses the [python.org](https://www.python.org/) 3.12 install.

Upstream: [milla-jovovich/mempalace](https://github.com/milla-jovovich/mempalace) — v3.1.0 release notes cover security fixes, MCP validation, SQLite/WAL, KG fixes, etc.

**CLI** (`mempalace mine`, `mempalace status`, …): run with the same venv Python or add that `Scripts` folder to PATH so you stay on the same version as the MCP.

**Check for newer releases (no upgrade until PyPI shows a version above the pin):**

```powershell
& "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\venvs\mempalace\Scripts\python.exe" -m pip index versions mempalace
```

Compare with [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/milla-jovovich/mempalace/releases). When a new stable `3.x` appears, update `~/.cursor/requirements-mempalace-mcp.txt`, reinstall into the venv, restart the MemPalace MCP in Cursor, and refresh MCP tool descriptors if Cursor does not pick up new tools automatically.
